FOOL YOURSELF bobbled ever so slightly at the start, was forwardly-placed between runners chasing two to four wide early, steadily weakened while being asked outside the three-eighths and continued to fade. FEATHERS (IRE) exchanged a very light bump at the start, raced at the back off the inside, was never near enough to threaten. MATOULA exchanged very light contact at the start, pursued from outside foes mid-pack three to four wide early, dropped back and shifted in a bit, tired.
